The role will go to a non-executive director. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Tito Mboweni has announced a major change at the Public Investment Corporation. From now on, the deputy finance minister or any other minister will no longer occupy the position of PIC chairperson. The role of PIC chairperson will go to a non-executive director. WATCH: Former PIC CEO Dan Matjila to continue testimony “Based on my experience of how boards of directors are supposed to operate, it was a bad decision but it had a reason,” Mboweni said. Sindi Mabaso-Kotana has been appointed as the interim board deputy chairperson while Dr Reuel Khoza has been appointed as chairperson of the PIC’s interim board.